17 or 35-8-20.1 from the date of initial appointment to the date by which such training is
18 to be completed pursuant to the applicable Code section;
19 (D) An elected sheriff who has assumed the office of sheriff and has not completed the
20 requirements for certification as a peace officer as provided in Chapter 8 of Title 35
21 from the date the oath of office was taken to the date by which such certification is to
22 be obtained pursuant to Code Section 15-16-1; and
23 (E) A federal law enforcement officer who is employed by the United States
24 government as a full-time law enforcement officer, is in good standing with his or her
25 federal agency of employment, is authorized to carry a firearm in the performance of
26 his or her official duties, and is empowered to arrest a person for criminal violations of
27 the United States Code."
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
